  "prompt": "Where did Adam and Eve live?",
  "response": "According to the biblical narrative, Adam and Eve lived in the Garden of Eden, a paradise created by God. The Garden of Eden is described in the Book of Genesis (Genesis 2:8-15) as a lush and abundant place where Adam and Eve were placed to tend and care for it. They were given everything they needed, but they were forbidden to eat from the tree of the knowledge of good and evil. After they disobeyed God by eating the forbidden fruit, they were expelled from the Garden of Eden (Genesis 3:23-24). \n\nThe exact location of the Garden of Eden is unknown and has been a subject of speculation and interpretation for centuries. The biblical text mentions that it was situated near four rivers: the Pishon, Gihon, Tigris, and Euphrates, which has led some to suggest it may have been in Mesopotamia (modern-day Iraq). However, this remains uncertain and is often considered more symbolic than literal.",
